### Test 2: Multiple blockquotes with image after
- Input: Email + BQ1 + BQ2 (contains image anchor)
- BQ1: has BQ2 text after it → fails test → result remains null  
- BQ2: nothing after it → passes test → result = BQ2
- **Expected**: BQ2 is selected ✅

### Test 3: Content after blockquote
- Input: Email + BQ1 + Text
- BQ1: has trailing text → fails test → result remains null
- No more blockquotes
- **Expected**: [fullContent, ''] returned ✅

### Test 4: Image anchor after blockquote
- Input: Email + BQ1 + Image
- BQ1: has trailing image → fails test → result remains null
- No more blockquotes
- **Expected**: [fullContent, ''] returned ✅

## Code Quality
- ✅ No syntax errors
- ✅ TypeScript types are correct
- ✅ Variable scoping is appropriate (testResult is local to each iteration)
- ✅ Backward compatible with existing email formats
- ✅ Handles all edge cases correctly

## Conclusion
The fix correctly implements the requirement to select the **last** blockquote with no trailing content, instead of the **first** one. This resolves the bug where email content following blockquotes was incorrectly hidden or misclassified.
